Book of Hours, Use of Utrecht

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 132. Southern Netherlands, Circa 1500. This manuscript is a Book of Hours for the Use of Utrecht, written in Dutch and Latin in hybrida script circa 1500, with full floral borders inhabited by a variety of creatures marking the major textual divisions and many hour divisions. The texts include the Hours of the Virgin, Penitential Psalms and Litany, and Office of the Dead, all in the translations of Gerard Groote, but also the Hours for the Days of the Week in Latin and prayers in both Dutch and Latin.
